                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Blodgett, Walton/165: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain (<persName type="from"
                            >Bowers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-11T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 11, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 11—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Department’s telegram No. 61, December 26, 6 p.m.<note n="48"
                        xml:id="d527fn48">Not printed.</note> Trial held and concluded before the
                    Supreme Court this morning. Decision expected any time within 8 days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
